	<fdd:sustainabilityFactors>
		<fdd:disclosure>Open standard. Developed by the Society of Motion Picture and Television Engineers (SMPTE), a member of the American National Standards Institute (ANSI).</fdd:disclosure>
		<fdd:documentation>SMPTE 378M-2004, Material Exchange Format (MXF) -- Operational pattern 1A (Single Item, Single Package)</fdd:documentation>
		<fdd:adoption>
			<p>OP1a is supported in many commercial devices and systems.  It is central to various MXF Application Specifications (profiles from user communities), including the Public Broadcasting System, the initial developer of <a href="http://www.amwa.tv/projects/AS-03.shtml">AS-03</a>, for use in the non-real-time distribution of programs to member stations.  The <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20040216125228/http:/www.media-matters.net/products-samma.php">SAMMA</a> device used to reformat videotapes outputs OP1a files.</p>
		</fdd:adoption>
